page=news_item&px=OpenMandriva-Lx-4.0-Alpha|title=OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 Alpha Surfaces|website=www.phoronix.com|language=en|access-date=2018-09-07}}</ref> || 6 September 2018 || 4.18\n|-\n| 3.0 RC1<ref>[https://blog.openmandriva.org/2016/07/openmandriva-lx-3-0-rc1-arrives/ OpenMandriva Lx 3.0 RC1 arrives!! &#8211; OMA blog]</ref> || 19 July 2016 || 4.6.4\n|-\n| 3.0 Beta 2<ref>[https://blog.openmandriva.org/2016/06/openmandriva-lx-3-0-beta2-is-here/ OpenMandriva Lx 3.0 Beta2 is here! &#8211; OMA blog]</ref> || 27 June 2016 || 4.6.2\n|-\n| 3.0 Beta 1<ref>[https://blog.openmandriva.org/2016/04/beta1-is-here/ Beta1 is here! &#8211; OMA blog]</ref> || 6 April 2016 || {{N/A}}\n|-\n| 3.0 Alpha<ref>[https://blog.openmandriva.org/2015/04/mixing-the-ingredients-together-announcing-openmandriva-lx-3-alpha/ Mixing the Ingredients Together \u2013 Announcing OpenMandriva Lx 3 Alpha &#8211; OMA blog]</ref> || 24 April 2015 || 3.18.11\n|-\n| 3.0 Pre-Alpha<ref>[https://blog.openmandriva.org/2015/02/pre-alpha-oma-lx3-is-here-hot-and-fresh/ Pre-Alpha OMA Lx3 is here \u2013 hot and fresh! &#8211; OMA blog]</ref> || 3 February 2015 || {{N/A}}\n|-\n| 2014.0 RC1<ref>[https://blog.openmandriva.org/en/2014/04/rc1-is-released/ RC1 is released! &#8211; OMA blog]</ref> || 18 April 2014 || 3.13.10\n|-\n| 2014.0 Beta<ref>[http://blog.openmandriva.org/2014/03/openmandriva-lx-2014-0-beta-is-here/ OpenMandriva Lx 2014.0 Beta is here! &#8211; OMA blog]</ref> || 24 March 2014 || 3.13.6\n|-\n| 2014.0 Alpha 2<ref>[http://blog.openmandriva.org/en/2014/02/winter-ended/ Winter ended &#8211; OMA blog]</ref> || 28 February 2014 || 3.12.13\n|-\n| 2014.0 Alpha<ref>[http://blog.openmandriva.org/en/2014/01/2014-alpha-carneval-time/ 2014 Alpha \u2013 Carneval time!]</ref> || 31 January 2014 || 3.12.8\n|}\n\n=== OpenMandriva Lx 2013.0 ===\n[[File:OpenMandriva_LX_2013.png|thumb|OpenMandriva Lx 2013.0]]\nOpenMandriva Lx 2013.0 was released on November 22, 2013 with codename \"Oxygen\".<ref name=\"distrowatch1\"/><ref name=\"linuxbsdos1\"/><ref name=\"mylinuxexplore1\"/><ref name=\"navychristian1\"/>\n\nThis version was the first release of OpenMandriva Lx, and was the [[Fork (software development)|fork]] of [[Mandriva Linux]] 2011.0. The version includes [[KDE]] 4.11.2. Menu in OpenMandriva Lx 2013.0 was SimpleWelcome, and also this version included media player [[ROSA Linux|ROSA Media Player]] 1.6, [[Mozilla Firefox]] 25.0, [[LibreOffice]] 4.1.3 and the [[Linux kernel]] 3.11.6.\n\n=== OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 ===\nOpenMandriva Lx 4.0 will support ARM64 (aarch64) and ARM v7 (armv7hnl) architectures.<ref name=\"softp240\" /><ref name=\"summer2018\" /> After arriving [[RISC-V]] board, OpenMandriva will start porting distribution to open source CPUs.<ref name=\"summer2018\" />\n\nThe first alpha version of OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 was released on September 6, 2018.<ref name=\"phoronix-4.0alpha\" />\n\nThe OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 Major Release Alpha 1 was released on December 25, 2018<ref name=\"openmandrivalx4.0a1\" />, the Beta was released on February 9, 2019<ref name=\"openmandrivalx4beta\" /> and the Release Candidate was released on May 12, 2019<ref name=\"openmandrivalx4rc\" />.\n\nThe OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 final release was announced on 16th June 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.openmandriva.org/en/news/article/the-best-until-openmandriva-does-better-released-omlx-4-0|title=Lx 4.0 release|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn this version, OpenMandriva Association announced that OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 have switched to RPMv4 and [[DNF (software)|dnf]] has replaced [[urpmi]].<ref name=\"openmandrivalx4.0a1\" /> Due to that, [[rpmdrake]] also has replaced by Dnfdragora.<ref name=\"openmandrivalx4beta\" />\n\n== Screenshots ==\n<gallery>\nFile:OpenMandriva_LX_2013.png|OpenMandriva Lx 2013.0\nFile:OpenMandriva_Lx_2014_Phosphorus.png|OpenMandriva Lx 2014.0\nFile:Small screenshot of OpenMandriva Lx 3.0 Einsteinium.jpg|OpenMandriva Lx 3.0\nFile:OpenMandriva_Lx_3.03.jpg|OpenMandriva Lx 3.03\n</gallery>\n\n=== More screenshots ===\n\n* [https://gallery.openmandriva.org/index.php?/category/31 OpenMandriva Gallery]\n* [https://www.opensourcefeed.org/1-openmandriva-lx4-release-screenshots/ OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 screenshots]\n\n==See also==\n* [[ROSA Linux]]\n* [[Mageia]]\n* [[PCLinuxOS]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official website}}\n* [http://forum.openmandriva.org OpenMandriva Lx Forum]\n* [https://wiki.openmandriva.org/ OpenMandriva Lx Wiki]\n* [https://issues.openmandriva.org/ OpenMandriva Lx Bugzilla]\n* [https://matrix.to/#/#openmandriva:matrix.org OpenMandriva Matrix Room]\n*[https://www.opensourcefeed.org/distribution/openmandriva OpenMandriva on OpenSourceFeed Gallery]\n{{Linux distributions}}\n\n[[Category:KDE]]\n[[Category:Mandriva Linux]]\n[[Category:RPM-based Linux distributions]]\n[[Category:X86-64 Linux distributions]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox OS\n| name = OpenMandriva Lx\n| logo = Oma-logo-22042013 300pp.png\n| logo_size = x70px\n| screenshot = File:Openmandriva.png\n| caption = OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 Einsteinium with KDE Plasma 5 interface\n| developer = OpenMandriva Association and Cooker group\n| family = [[Unix-like]] (originally based on [[Mandriva Linux]])\n| working_state = Current\n| source_model = [[Open-source software|Open source]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://github.com/OpenMandrivaAssociation/|title=OpenMandriva Association|website=GitHub|language=en|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref>\n| released = {{Start date and age|2013|11|22}}\n| latest release version = Lx 4.1<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.openmandriva.org/en/news/article/and-openmandriva-did-better-omlx-4-1-final-release-is-out-now|title=OMLx 4.1 final release is out now!|date=2020-02-01|access-date=2020-02-09|}}</ref>\n| latest release date = {{Start date and age|2020|02|01}}\n| latest preview version =\n| latest preview date = <--{{Start date and age|2019|11|10}}-->\n| updatemodel = dnf (command line) and dnfdragora (GUI)\n| package_manager = [[RPM Package Manager#RPM.org|RPM.org]] (RPMv4)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://forum.openmandriva.org/t/switching-to-rpmv4/1702|title=Switching to RPMv4|publisher=OMA Forum|accessdate=16 May 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"openmandrivalx4.0a1\" />\n| supported_platforms = [[IA-32]], [[x86-64]], [[i586]], [[ARM architecture|ARM]], [[ARM architecture|ARMv8-A]]\n| kernel_type = [[Monolithic kernel|Monolithic]] ([[Linux kernel|Linux]])\n| userland = [[GNU Core Utilities|GNU]]\n| ui = [[KDE Plasma 5]], [[KDE Plasma 4]], [[LXQt]]\n| license = [[Free software]] (mainly [[GPL]])\n}}\n'''OpenMandriva Lx''' is a [[Linux distribution]] forked from [[Mandriva Linux]].  It is published by the OpenMandriva Association.\n\n== History ==\n===Origin of the distribution===\nOpenMandriva Lx is a community [[Linux]] distribution. Originally an offering of [[Mandriva Linux]], the OpenMandriva product was created in May, 2012, when [[Mandriva|Mandriva S.A.]] avoided bankruptcy by abandoning the development of its consumer product to the Mandriva community.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.mandriva.com/en/2012/05/17/mandriva-linux-will-return-to-the-community/ |url-status=dead |title=Mandriva SA official blog: Mandriva Linux will return to the community |date=17 May 2012 |accessdate=2015-12-13 |publisher=[[Mandriva]] |archive-date=2015-05-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150523070604/https://blog.mandriva.com/en/2012/05/17/mandriva-linux-will-return-to-the-community/ }}</ref><ref>[https://distrowatch.com/weekly.php?issue=20121217#news DistroWatch Weekly, Issue 487, 17 December 2012]</ref> The first stable version (OpenMandriva Lx 2013 \"Oxygen\") was released in late 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://distrowatch.com/8172|title=Distribution Release: OpenMandriva Lx 2013.0 )|first=|last=|publisher=DistroWatch}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ostatic.com/blog/first-community-openmandriva-released|title=First Community OpenMandriva Released|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140423050211/http://ostatic.com/blog/first-community-openmandriva-released|archivedate=2014-04-23}}</ref>\n\n===OpenMandriva Association===\nThe OpenMandriva Association was established on December 12, 2012 under [[:fr:Loi 1901|1901 French law]], to represent the OpenMandriva Community.<ref>[https://www.openmandriva.org/en/documentation/association/About?q=%2Fabout About - OpenMandriva]</ref> It manages free software projects including OpenMandriva Lx.\n\n=== OpenMandriva Lx development environment ===\nOpenMandriva Lx's development environment is an ABF (Automated Build Farm) which can manage the source codes, compile it to binaries. Also ABF creates the package repository and ISO images.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blog.openmandriva.org/2016/04/brand-new-openmandriva-development-environment-abf|title=Brand new OpenMandriva development environment \u2013 ABF! \u2013 OMA blog|website=blog.openmandriva.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://distrowatch.com/dwres.php?resource=showheadline&story=250|title=OpenMandriva opens build farm|last=DistroWatch|website=distrowatch.com|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref>\n\n==Versions==\nIn late 2013, the first version of OpenMandriva Lx was released. It was based on Mandriva Linux 2011, which was itself an amalgamation of [[ROSA Linux]] and Mandriva SA.<ref name=\"distrowatch1\">{{cite web|url=http://distrowatch.com/weekly.php?issue=20131209#feature|title=DistroWatch Weekly|first=|last=|publisher=DistroWatch}}</ref><ref name=\"linuxbsdos1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.linuxbsdos.com/2013/11/30/openmandriva-lx-2013-0-review/|title=OpenMandriva Lx 2013.0 review - LinuxBSDos.com|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"mylinuxexplore1\">{{cite web|url=http://mylinuxexplore.blogspot.fr/2013/11/openmandriva-lx-20130-review-looks.html|title=Linuxed - Exploring Linux distros: OpenMandriva Lx 2013.0 Review: Looks awesome but needs to improve functionality and performance|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"navychristian1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.navychristian.org/2013/11/openmandriva-lx-20130-review.html|title=The Navy Christian: OpenMandriva Lx 2013.0 Review|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nOpenMandriva Lx 2014 \"Phosphorus\" was released on 1 May 2014.<ref name=\"blogopenmandriva20140\">{{cite web|url=https://blog.openmandriva.org/en/2014/05/a-breath-of-fresh-air-with-a-kde-soul-openmandriva%C2%AD-lx-2014-is-burning-free/|title=\u201cA Breath of Fresh Air with a KDE Soul\u201d* \u2013 OpenMandriva Lx 2014 is burning free! |publisher= OpenMandriva Association}}</ref><ref name=\"distrowatch2\">{{cite web|url=http://distrowatch.com/weekly.php?issue=20140602#feature|title=DistroWatch Weekly|first=|last=|publisher=DistroWatch}}</ref><ref name=\"dasublog\">{{cite web|url=http://dasublogbyprashanth.blogspot.fr/2014/05/review-openmandriva-lx-20140.html|title=Das U-Blog by Prashanth: Review: OpenMandriva Lx 2014.0|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"hectic1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hecticgeek.com/2014/05/openmandriva-lx-2014-0-review/|title='OpenMandriva Lx 2014.0' Review - Slow to Boot, High Memory Consumption, But Responsive & Easy to Configure|date=4 May 2014|publisher=}}</ref> The release had a very positive review from one of the founders of the initial [[Mandrake Linux]] distribution, [[Ga\u00ebl Duval]].<ref name=\"duval\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indidea.org/gael/blog/?p=444|title=A quick tour of OpenMandriva Lx 2014.0 (Phosphorus)}}</ref>\n\nOpenMandriva Lx 2014.2, codenamed \"The Scion\", a bugfix release for 2014.1, was released on 29 June 2015.<ref name=\"blogopenmandriva20142\">{{cite web|url=https://blog.openmandriva.org/2015/06/the-scion-is-ready/|title=The Scion is ready! \u00bb OMA blog|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"blogopenmandrivatribute\">{{cite web|url=https://blog.openmandriva.org/en/2015/05/tribute-to-mandrake/|title=Tribute to Mandrake \u00bb OMA blog|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"distrowatch3\">{{cite web|url=http://distrowatch.com/8997|title=Distribution Release: OpenMandriva Lx 2014.2|first=|last=|publisher=DistroWatch}}</ref><ref name=\"softpedia1\">{{cite web|url=http://news.softpedia.com/news/openmandriva-lx-2014-2-officially-released-as-a-tribute-to-mandrake-linux-485733.shtml|title=OpenMandriva Lx 2014.2 Officially Released as a Tribute to Mandrake Linux|first=Marius|last=Nestor|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"phoronix1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=OpenMandriva-Lx-2014.2|title=OpenMandriva Lx 2014.2 \"The Scion\" Pays Tribute To Mandrake |publisher=Phoronix}}</ref>\n\nDuring 2015, OpenMandriva released an alpha version of OpenMandriva Lx 2015. As the operating system was developed all 2015 year, in 2016, the version was released as OpenMandriva Lx 3.0 Beta.<ref name=\"blogopenmandriva30beta\">[https://blog.openmandriva.org/2016/06/openmandriva-lx-3-0-beta2-is-here/ OpenMandriva Lx 3.0 Beta 2 is here! - OMA blog]</ref> This new release came with significant changes to the core system \u2014 among other things, it was the first desktop Linux distribution that was built completely with the [[Clang]] compiler instead of GCC.<ref>[https://distrowatch.com/dwres.php?resource=showheadline&story=463 OpenMandriva uses Clang], '''DistroWatch'''</ref>\n\nA stable and final release of OpenMandriva Lx 3.0 was released in August 2016,<ref name=\"blogopenmandriva30\">{{Cite web|url=https://blog.openmandriva.org/2016/08/openmandriva-lx-3-0-final-release-is-out/|title=OpenMandriva Lx 3.0 Final Release is out! \u2013 OMA blog|website=blog.openmandriva.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref><ref name=\"dwweekly2016\">[https://distrowatch.com/weekly.php?issue=20160919#openmandriva DistroWatch Weekly, Issue 679, 19 September 2016]</ref> followed by 3.01 in December 2016<ref name=\"blogopenmandriva301\">[https://blog.openmandriva.org/2016/12/openmandriva-lx-3-01-our-holidays-gift/ OpenMandriva Lx 3.01 - our holidays gift - OMA blog]</ref><ref name=\"linuxbsdos301\">[http://linuxbsdos.com/2017/01/02/openmandriva-lx-3-01-review/ OpenMandriva Lx 3.01 review | LinuxBSDos.com]</ref> and 3.02 in June 2017.<ref name=\"openmandriva302\">[https://www.openmandriva.org/en/news/article/a-proud-scion-of-name-openmandriva-lx-3-02-release/ A proud scion of name: OpenMandriva Lx 3.02 release - OpenMandriva]</ref> This was followed by OpenMandriva Lx 3.03, which was released in November 2017.<ref name=\"openmandriva303\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.openmandriva.org/en/news/article/openmandriva-lx-3-03-get-it-while-it-s-hot|title=OpenMandriva Lx 3.03 - Get it while it\u2019s hot! - OpenMandriva|website=www.openmandriva.org|language=en|access-date=2017-11-23}}</ref><ref name=\"distrowatch303\">[https://distrowatch.com/?newsid=10036 Distribution Release: OpenMandriva Lx 3.03 (DistroWatch.com News)]</ref>\n\nAfter releasing OpenMandriva Lx 3.03, OpenMandriva Lx developers started dropping support of i586 processor architecture in OpenMandriva Lx 4.0.<ref name=\"openmandriva303\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=OpenMandriva-Dropping-32-bit|title=OpenMandriva Is Going To Do Away With 32-bit Support - Phoronix|website=www.phoronix.com|language=en|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref>\n\nThe development of OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 continued on for two years after Lx 3.03 was released.<ref name=\"openmandrivaplans40\">[https://www.openmandriva.org/en/news/article/openmandriva-upcoming-release-plans-for-lx-3-03-and-lx-4-0 OpenMandriva upcoming release plans for Lx 3.03 and Lx 4.0 \u2014 OpenMandriva]</ref><ref name=\"40wiki\">[https://wiki.openmandriva.org/en/4.0 4.0 \u2014 Wiki en OpenMandriva]</ref><ref name=\"phoronix40\">[https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=OpenMandriva-Lx-4.0-Prepping OpenMandriva 4.0 Being Prepared With zSTD-Enabled Linux 4.16, Clang Pre-7.0, GCC 8 - Phoronix]</ref><ref name=\"softp40\">[https://news.softpedia.com/news/openmandriva-lx-4-0-planned-linux-kernel-4-12-coming-to-openmandriva-lx-3-users-516890.shtml OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 Planned, Linux Kernel 4.12 Comes to OpenMandriva Lx 3 Users], '''Softpedia News'''</ref><ref name=\"summer2018\">[https://www.openmandriva.org/en/news/article/summer-news Summer news - OpenMandriva]</ref><ref name=\"201828dev\">[https://www.openmandriva.org/en/news/article/development-news-week-2018-28 Development news Week 2018-28 - OpenMandriva]</ref><ref name=\"softp240\">[https://news.softpedia.com/news/openmandriva-lx-4-launching-soon-with-kde-plasma-5-13-gcc-8-1-and-linux-4-18-521867.shtml OpenMandriva Lx 4 Launching Soon with KDE Plasma 5.13, GCC 8.1, and Linux 4.18], '''Softpedia News'''</ref><ref name=\"phoronix240\">[https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=OpenMandriva-LX4-Approaching OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 Is Approaching With DNF/RPM4, KDE Plasma 5.13, Linux 4.17~4.18 - Phoronix]</ref>\n\nThe OpenMandriva Lx 4.0 stable release arrived in June 2019.<ref name=\"blogopenmandriva40\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.openmandriva.org/en/news/article/the-best-until-openmandriva-does-better-released-omlx-4-0|title=The best, until OpenMandriva does better: released OMLx 4.0 - OpenMandriva|website=www.openmandriva.org|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-23}}</ref> Among many other changes, this release is notable for switching to the [[DNF_(software)|DNF package manager]] for software management<ref name=\"omv4urpm2dnf\">{{Cite web|url=https://wiki.openmandriva.org/en/4.0/Release_Notes#Package_Management_.28change_from_URPMI_to_DNF.29|title=4.0/Release Notes - Wiki [en] OpenMandriva|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-23}}</ref>, including [[Mageia]]'s dnfdragora to replace rpmdrake.<ref name=\"openmandrivalx4beta\" />\n\n=== Version history ===\n<!-- Template:Version - for version & release history. Documentation and examples: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Version -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin-left:1em; margin-right:0\"\n|-\n! Version !! Code name<ref name=\"release-list\" /> !! Release date<ref name=\"